&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a qualified nurse to join our North West Community Nursing team. We are looking for a caring, motivated and adaptable nurse to join our busy, professional and dynamic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should display a commitment to interdisciplinary team working and strive to deliver excellent standards of care to people in their own environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to demonstrate a real enthusiasm for community nursing, as well as a desire for on-going professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to travel independently across the region to fulfil the requirements of the post is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a permanent full time post of 37.5 hours a week covering a 7 day service, on a rota system.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information please contact Team leader Jayne Richards on 01691 663609 or jayne.richards@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
